subSubSection.paragraph:
Gnathosoma

. Fixed digit of chelicera with one small tooth close to terminal hook, pilus dentilis not discernible; movable digit not distinct, fully transformed into long, curved spermatodactyl (
78–82 µm
), progressively tapering into a blunt apex; dorsal seta conspicuous, markedly enlarged (
Fig. 32
). Other gnathosomal structures similar to those in female.
